Challenge Questions:
1. How can you ensure the weather updates automatically at regular intervals?
Using setInterval(updateWeather, 180000) to call updateWeather function and display the results every 3minutes
2. What is the best way to generate random values for the weather properties?
Using Math.floor(Math.random() * <max number>)
3. How can you dynamically check for extreme weather conditions and update warnings?
using if function checking for the extreme conditions and updating a message on the website 
if (
      currentWeather.condition === "Snow" &&
      currentWeather.temperature <= -10
    ) {
      document.getElementById(
        "weather-animation"
      ).innerText = `Do not go outside!`;
    
4. How will you structure the CSS so the warning message stands out?
I added dark background and set the font color to red
